## ⚡ Atomic Task Execution

**CRITICAL:** Execute tasks atomically with proper validation at each step.

### Atomic Task Workflow

For EVERY task:

```bash
# 1. Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/P{phase}-{domain}-{task-number}

# 2. Write tests FIRST (TDD)
# Create *_test.go files

# 3. Run tests (should fail - RED)
go test ./internal/domain/{domain}/...

# 4. Implement minimal code (GREEN)
# Write actual implementation

# 5. Run tests again (should pass)
go test ./internal/domain/{domain}/...

# 6. Refactor if needed
# Clean up code, optimize

# 7. Run ALL tests
go test ./...

# 8. Check coverage
go test -cover ./... | grep -E "coverage: [0-9]+\.[0-9]+%"

# 9. Lint code
golangci-lint run ./internal/domain/{domain}/...

# 10. Build project
go build ./...

# 11. Manual UI testing (if applicable)
# Start dev server and test in UI

# 12. Commit with conventional commit message
git add .
git commit -m "feat(domain): implement task P{phase}-{task-number}"

# 13. Push to remote
git push origin feature/P{phase}-{domain}-{task-number}
```

### Pre-Commit Checklist

**MANDATORY before EVERY commit:**

- [ ] All tests pass (`go test ./...`)
- [ ] Coverage meets minimum threshold
- [ ] No linter errors (`golangci-lint run`)
- [ ] Code builds successfully (`go build ./...`)
- [ ] Integration tests pass (if applicable)
- [ ] Manual UI testing completed (if UI changes)
- [ ] Synthetic data generated (if new entity)

